Package com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.util.config

Class Config_Benchmark

java.lang.Object
com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.util.config.Config_Benchmark
public class Config_Benchmark extends Object
Utility class to handle configuration settings and related operations for benchmarking and testing. This class contains methods for setting up and retrieving configuration details, as well as providing default settings for various parameters.

  • Method Details

    • getSeed

      public static long getSeed(Config config)
      Retrieves the seed value from the configuration. If the seed value is not explicitly set or cannot be retrieved, the current system time in milliseconds is used as the default value.
      Returns:
      the seed value as a long, or the current system time in milliseconds if not specified.

    • isInstrumented

      public static boolean isInstrumented(Config config)
      Method to determine if this configuration has an instrumented helper. NOTE: we would prefer to place this logic in the Helper class but we put it here for now.
      Returns:
      true if helper is instrumented

    • setupConfig

      public static Config setupConfig(String instrumenting, String fixes, String seed, String inversions, String cutoff, String interimInversions)
      Configures and sets up a new Config object based on the input parameters. The configuration includes various settings for instrumentation, seed, cutoffs, inversions, fixes, and interim inversions.
      Parameters:
      instrumenting - the instrumenting value used for configuration, applied to multiple metrics such as swaps, compares, and copies.
      fixes - the value that specifies the number of fixes to be configured.
      seed - the seed value used for initialization in the configuration.
      inversions - the inversions setting to be applied within the configuration.
      cutoff - the cutoff value used for configuring the benchmark helper.
      interimInversions - the value for interim inversions used in the configuration.
      Returns:
      a new Config object containing the configured settings.

    • setupConfig2

      public static Config setupConfig2(String instrumenting, String seed, String inversions, String cutoff, String interimInversions, String insurance, String noCopy)
      Configures and sets up a new Config object based on the provided parameters. The configuration includes various settings such as instrumentation, seed, inversions, cutoffs, interim inversions, insurance, and whether copying is disabled.
      Parameters:
      instrumenting - the instrumenting value to be applied within the configuration, used for metrics such as swaps, compares, and copies.
      seed - the seed value used for initialization in the configuration.
      inversions - the value specifying the inversions setting for the configuration.
      cutoff - the cutoff value used for configuring the helper in the benchmark.
      interimInversions - the value for interim inversions used in the configuration.
      insurance - the insurance value for additional configuration.
      noCopy - the value indicating whether copying is disabled in the configuration.
      Returns:
      a new Config object containing the configured settings.

    • setupConfigFixes

      public static Config setupConfigFixes()
      Configures and sets up a new Config object with predefined settings. This method initializes a configuration with specific options, including enabling instrumented helpers, setting a default cutoff value, and enabling fixes during instrumentation.
      Returns:
      a new Config object pre-configured with the defined settings.
